content.description: A proud line up the SW face of the tower which faces the wash. Very sunny and warm. The line starts on a chossy, right trending flake system with hard to clip bolts too far to the left. After the flake, move left and up through some sandy but quality cruxes. The route has an intermediate anchor to lower, but climbs to the top of the tower.
content.protection: 18 bolts. Lower twice unless you have an 80M+ rope.
content.location: Second from the left on the SW face of the tower. Look for the right trending crack

content.description: Very steep, long, and sustained routes on the face that you see from the wash. This portion of the wall holds many hard lines up to 5.14. Very sunny, catch it on a cloudy day or shoulder season.
